<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD51FF9F9E8FFF12DD6DDBAD" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD51FF9F9E8FFF12DE53DA95" bold="true" box="[199,270,151,177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Head.</emphasis>
Antenna with at least 18 flagellomeres (apex missing); first flagellomere ca 1.1× length of second flagellomere. Face granulose. Clypeus granulose, convex, apical margin truncated, blunt. Malar space granulose, ca 0.4× basal width of mandible. Upper tooth of mandible slightly longer than lower tooth, with a weak lamella. Frons granulose and without median carina. Vertex granulose. Interocellar distance equal to ocello-ocular distance and 2.5× distance between median and lateral ocelli; distance between lateral ocelli and eyes ca 1.2 
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD51FF9F9B49FEA2DA49DB64" box="[1281,1300,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">×</emphasis>
longer than diameter of ocellus. Temple mat, ca 0.5× as long as eyes in lateral view. Occipital carina evenly arched, reaching hypostomal carina at mandible base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD51FF9F9E8FFE16DC18D845" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD51FF9F9E8FFE16DE11DB89" bold="true" box="[199,332,403,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Pronotum granulose-punctate dorsally and transversely striate laterally. Mesoscutum granulose, notauli absent. Scutellum granulose-punctate, metanotum granulose. Mesopleuron punctate, punctures separated by their diameter, finely transversely striate below tegula, speculum smooth and shiny. Metapleuron punctate and interspaces smooth. Propodeum with area basalis trapezoid; area superomedia hexagonal, slightly longer than wide and separated from area petiolaris; area superomedia flat, granulose-rugulose; costula relatively weak; propodeal spiracle oval, connected to pleural carina by a distinct carina.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD51FF9F9E8FFDEFDE12D8D5" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD51FF9F9E8FFDEFDE52D8A0" bold="true" box="[199,271,618,644]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Wing.</emphasis>
Fore wing areolet absent; portion of vein M between 2rs-m and 2m-cu ca. 0.8× as long as 2rs-m. Marginal cell short, vein RS ca 2.3× longer than vein 2r&amp;RS. Vein 1cu-a slightly distad of M&amp;RS. External angles of second discal cell acute (65°). Hind wing with CU&amp;cu-a inclivous, 2-CU connected with CU&amp;cu-a, intercepted at lower 0.2 of its length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD51FF9F9E8FFD7EDDFDD91D" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD51FF9F9E8FFD7EDE5BD931" bold="true" box="[199,262,763,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Legs.</emphasis>
Hind femur 4.7× longer than wide. Inner spur of hind tibia ca 0.6× as long as first tarsomere of hind tarsus. Tarsal claws pectinate basally (
<figureCitation id="24E92A56BD51FF9F9C0AFC9ADDC9D91D" box="[578,660,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[306,1281,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[306,1281,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Breviterebra apicocrinis sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesopleuron, lateral view C propodeum, dorsal view D first metasomal segment, lateral view E ovipositor, lateral view F head, anterior view G head, dorsal view H mesoscutum, dorsal view I metasomal apical segments J hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531140/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Fig. 2J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD51FF9F9E8FFCC6DC41D9C9" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD51FF9F9E8FFCC6DE16D979" bold="true" box="[199,331,835,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Metasoma.</emphasis>
First segment with dorso-lateral carinae, ca 2.8× longer than width of postpetiole; petiole ca 2.2× longer than postpetiole. Second tergite ca 0.7× as long as first tergite, as long as its apical width; thyridium oval, its distance from basal margin of tergite about equal to its length. Third tergite ca 0.8× as long as its apical width. Ovipositor a little shorter than apical depth of metasoma, with a weak subapical notch on upper valve (
<figureCitation id="24E92A56BD51FF9F9B7EFC2ADAD2D9ED" box="[1334,1423,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[306,1281,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[306,1281,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Breviterebra apicocrinis sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesopleuron, lateral view C propodeum, dorsal view D first metasomal segment, lateral view E ovipositor, lateral view F head, anterior view G head, dorsal view H mesoscutum, dorsal view I metasomal apical segments J hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531140/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
); setose part of ovipositor sheath 0.4× as long as hind tibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD51FF9F9E8FFC73DA6DDE59" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD51FF9F9E8FFC73DE7DDE34" bold="true" box="[199,288,1014,1040]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Colour.</emphasis>
Black. Scape and pedicel black; mandible yellow except teeth reddish brown; palpi and tegula yellow; fore and mid legs from apical half of coxae on yellowish brown; basal half of fore and mid coxae blackish brown; hind coxa, trochanter and trochantellus black, femur and tibia yellowish brown with base and apex of tibia more or less infuscated, basal 0.9 of tarsi yellowish brown and remainder infuscated; metasoma entirely blackish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD51FF9F9E8FFB03DE49DECD" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD51FF9F9E8FFB03DE62DE84" bold="true" box="[199,319,1158,1184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Variation.</emphasis>
Propodeal costula varies from weak to strong; area superomedial slightly longer than wide to slightly wider than long; specimen from 
<collectingRegion id="7E16F831BD51FF9F9C2BFB2EDC40DEE1" box="[611,797,1195,1221]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Xizang province</collectingRegion>
has area petiolaris stronger rugulose than in the 
<collectingRegion id="7E16F831BD51FF9F9B0AFB2EDAC1DEE1" box="[1346,1436,1195,1221]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F4C86558BD51FF9F9E8FFB77DBABDF5E" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD51FF9F9E8FFB77DDD8DF2A" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1473]" box="[199,645,1266,1294]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD51FF9F9E8FFB77DE3CDF28" bold="true" box="[199,353,1266,1292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="C4C57643BD51FF9F9F2FFB76DEF7DF29" box="[359,426,1267,1293]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="7E16F831BD51FF9F9FF1FB76DD45DF29" box="[441,536,1267,1293]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="7E16F831BD51FF9F9C6BFB76DD24DF2A" box="[547,633,1267,1294]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Xizang</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD51FF9F9E8FFA93DEFADF71" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD51FF9F9E8FFA93DE3FDF14" bold="true" box="[199,354,1302,1328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Comparison.</emphasis>
This species differs distinctly from the only other known species of this genus, 
<taxonomicName id="7BD24D50BD51FF9F9A93FA92DA23DF15" authorityName="Kusigemati" authorityYear="1982" box="[1243,1406,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Breviterebra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticlypeata">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD51FF9F9A93FA92DA23DF15" box="[1243,1406,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">B. laticlypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as shown in the key above.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD51FF9F9E8FFADBDBABDF5E" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1473]" box="[199,1270,1374,1402]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD51FF9F9E8FFADBDED8DF5C" bold="true" box="[199,389,1374,1400]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">DNA Barcoding</emphasis>
: The COI sequence iss deposited in GenBank (accession number 
<accessionNumber id="A381AB30BD51FF9F9A2FFADADBB6DF5E" box="[1127,1259,1375,1402]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MZ647963" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">MZ647963</accessionNumber>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F4C86558BD51FF9F9E8FFA06DE1CDFE5" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD51FF9F9E8FFA06DE1CDFE5" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD51FF9F9E8FFA06DE13DFB9" bold="true" box="[199,334,1411,1437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name derived from apex (Latin for tip) and crinis (Greek for hair), because its metasoma is densely setose apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
